                <h2 class="helvetica"> How to Take Care of Your Dog</h2>
    
                <p class="helvetica">
                    Caring for a dog involves a commitment to their well-being,
                    ensuring they lead a healthy and happy life.
                    Whether you're a new pet owner or an experienced one,
                    it's essential to stay informed about best practices in dog care.
                    From regular vet visits and a balanced diet to exercise and grooming,
                    each aspect plays a crucial role in maintaining your dog's health.
                    Additionally, training and socialization help in developing good
                    behavior, while love and attention strengthen your bond.
                    Here are some concise tips to guide you in providing the best
                    care for your canine companion.
                </p>
    
                <div class="helvetica-3">
                    <ol>
                        <li> <span class="bold-color">Regular Vet Visits:</span> 
                            <ul>
                                <li>
                                    Schedule annual check-ups and vaccinations.
                                </li>
    
                                <li>
                                    Keep up with flea, tick, and heartworm prevention.
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li> <span class="bold-color">Balanced Diet:</span>
                            <ul>
                                <li>
                                    Feed high-quality, age-appropriate dog food.
                                </li>
    
                                <li>
                                    Avoid giving human food, especially toxic items like chocolate, grapes, and onions.
                                </li>
    
                                <li>
                                    Monitor your dog's weight and adjust food intake as needed.
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li> <span class="bold-color">Exercise:</span>
                            <ul>
                                <li>
                                    Provide daily physical activity tailored to your dog's breed and age.
                                </li>
    
                                <li>
                                    Include walks, playtime, and interactive toys.
                                </li>
    
                                <li>
                                    Ensure mental stimulation with puzzle toys and training sessions.
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li> <span class="bold-color">Grooming:</span>
                            <ul>
                                <li>
                                    Brush your dog's coat regularly to prevent matting and shedding.
                                </li>
    
                                <li>
                                    Bathe your dog with dog-specific shampoo as needed.
                                </li>
    
                                <li>
                                    Trim nails regularly to prevent overgrowth and discomfort.
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    Clean ears to prevent infections and remove wax buildup.
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    Brush teeth to maintain dental health and prevent gum disease.
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li> <span class="bold-color">Training and Socialization:</span>
                            <ul>
                                <li>
                                    Start training early and use positive reinforcement techniques.
                                </li>
    
                                <li>
                                    Socialize your dog with other dogs and people to build confidence and good behavior.
                                </li>
    
                                <li>
                                    Enroll in obedience classes if needed for structured training.
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
